  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves several key aspects:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. Domestic Legal Structures\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Proceeds of Crime legislation\n- Mandatory reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Regulatory Components\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols\n\n4. Criminal Penalties\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Potential prison sentences\n- Asset seizure\n- Professional license revocation\n\n5. Financial Institution Obligations\n- Implement compliance programs\n- Conduct risk assessments\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Report suspicious activities\n\n6. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Law enforcement collaboration\n- Cross-border information sharing\n- Investigative procedures\n\n7. Prevention Strategies\n- Risk-based approach\n- Enhanced due diligence\n- Technology-driven monitoring systems\n- Staff training and awareness programs\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities globally.",
